  * Terminal: one-shot resume command with permission-mode flags.
  * Sessions list: a Model column shows which model produced each session.
  * Search: match snippets lead with the keyword so it survives row clipping.
  * Rename: gated at the dialog's OK button rather than the menu item and re-enabled live when the session stops; reworked as a path-only lib/ unit plus CLI that refreshes the scan cache.
  * Move: the chooser's relative result is anchored to an absolute path.
  * Scan: recover a session title that sits past the tail window.
  * Debug: a gated -debug diagnostic log.

 -- Weiwu Zhang <a@colourful.land>  Tue, 09 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

questlog (1.1.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * CLI: the --json search composes by one boolean algebra. Each content condition is a needle in an optional region-list: --keyword and --regex (aliases --kw, --rx, and the former --search, --pattern). Clauses AND by adjacency, --or widens to OR, --not negates the next clause.
  * CLI: --scope is gone; a :regions suffix rides on each keyword or regex clause instead. Region tokens are user, assistant, tool-use, tool-result, and any, comma-joined for OR and accepting unambiguous prefixes.
  * CLI: --case makes keyword matching case-sensitive; a query that needs grouping is rejected rather than mis-parsed.
  * CLI: --shortstat emits a totals summary (session and subagent counts, turns, tokens, total cost) over the same result set as --json.
  * CLI: the default --limit is removed; a query returns every matching session unless --limit caps it.
  * CLI: --json emits null for an unknown cost rather than the -1.0 sentinel.
  * Time filter unified across the CLI and GUI: --since takes a relative window (24h, 7d, 2w) or an absolute date (2026-04-01); the GUI time row gains a custom member with a date-picker popover.
  * Packaging: the cli/ scripts are installed so --json and --shortstat work from packages; the Homebrew formula also installs config.tcl.

 -- Weiwu Zhang <a@colourful.land>  Tue, 02 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

